analyst_recommendation_change_score_2.description: A score representing changes in analyst recommendations for an entity.

composite_story_sentiment_score_2.description: Combined sentiment score for a news story using multiple analysis techniques.

corporate_action_report_sentiment_score.description: Sentiment score for news about corporate action announcements.

earnings_evaluation_sentiment_score.description: Sentiment score for news about earnings evaluations.

earnings_release_sentiment_score.description: Sentiment score for news about earnings releases.

editorial_commentary_sentiment_score_2.description: Sentiment score for short commentary and editorials on equity markets.

entity_record_count_per_story.description: Total number of entity records published for a news story.

entity_relevance_score_2.description: A score indicating how strongly an entity is related to a news story.

event_novelty_score.description: Score indicating how new or unique a news story is within a 24-hour window.

event_sentiment_score_2.description: Granular score representing the sentiment of a news event for an entity.

global_equities_sentiment_score.description: Sentiment score for global equities news based on positive, neutral, or negative tone.

global_event_novelty_score.description: Score indicating the novelty of a news story across all providers within a 24-hour window.

global_novelty_elapsed_milliseconds.description: Milliseconds between the first and current story in a global novelty chain.

global_novelty_similarity_gap_days.description: Number of days since a similar story was detected across all sources.

merger_acquisition_sentiment_score_4.description: Sentiment score for news about mergers, acquisitions, and takeovers.

multi_classifier_equity_sentiment_score.description: Sentiment score based on the tone for the most relevant companies in a story.

mws50_acb.description: REPORTS ON CORPORATE ACTIONS (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given news story according to the BCA classifier, which specializes in reports on corporate action announcements

mws50_acb_2.description: REPORTS ON CORPORATE ACTIONS (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given news story according to the BCA classifier, which specializes in reports on corporate action announcements

mws50_aes.description: A granular score between 0 and 100 that represents the ratio of positive events reported on an entity compared to the total count of events (excluding neutral ones) measured over a rolling 91- day window in a particular package (Dow Jones, Web or PR Editions). Only news items that match a RavenPack event category receiving an ESS score are included in the computation of AES. An event with ESS>50 is counted as a positive entry whereas one with ESS<50 is counted as a negative entry. Events with ESS=50 are considered neutral and excluded from the computation.

mws50_aes_2.description: A granular score between 0 and 100 that represents the ratio of positive events reported on an entity compared to the total count of events (excluding neutral ones) measured over a rolling 91- day window in a particular package (Dow Jones, Web or PR Editions). Only news items that match a RavenPack event category receiving an ESS score are included in the computation of AES. An event with ESS>50 is counted as a positive entry whereas one with ESS<50 is counted as a negative entry. Events with ESS=50 are considered neutral and excluded from the computation.

mws50_bam.description: VENTURE, COMPANY, MERGERS & ACQUISITIONS (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given story according to the BAM classifier, which specializes in news stories about mergers, acquisitions, and takeovers

mws50_bam_2.description: VENTURE, COMPANY, MERGERS & ACQUISITIONS (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given story according to the BAM classifier, which specializes in news stories about mergers, acquisitions, and takeovers

mws50_bee.description: EARNINGS EVALUATIONS (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given story according to the BEE classifier, which specializes in news stories about earnings evaluations

mws50_bee_2.description: EARNINGS EVALUATIONS (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given story according to the BEE classifier, which specializes in news stories about earnings evaluations

mws50_ber.description: EARNINGS RELEASES (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given story according to the BER classifier, which specializes in news stories about earnings releases

mws50_ber_2.description: EARNINGS RELEASES (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given story according to the BER classifier, which specializes in news stories about earnings releases

mws50_category.description: A unique tag to label, identify, and recognize a particular type and property of an entity-specific news event

mws50_country_code.description: The two character ISO-3166 country code associated with an entity. Companies and organizations are associated with the country of incorporation, currencies are associated with the country where the central bank resides, and commodities are global and not associated with specific countries, so their COUNTRY_CODE label is 'XX'

mws50_country_code_2.description: The two character ISO-3166 country code associated with an entity. Companies and organizations are associated with the country of incorporation, currencies are associated with the country where the central bank resides, and commodities are global and not associated with specific countries, so their COUNTRY_CODE label is 'XX'

mws50_ens.description: EVENT NOVELTY SCORE - A score between 0 and 100 that represents how "new" or novel a news story is within a 24-hour time window across all news stories in a particular package

mws50_ens_2.description: EVENT NOVELTY SCORE - A score between 0 and 100 that represents how "new" or novel a news story is within a 24-hour time window across all news stories in a particular package

mws50_ens_elapsed.description: EVENT NOVELTY ELAPSED TIME - The number of milliseconds between the first story and the current story in an event novelty chain. The first story in a chain will always be given a value of zero milliseconds (ENS_ELAPSED = 0). Subsequent stories in the same event novelty chain will receive higher values indicating the number of milliseconds elapsed since the first news story reporting the event. ENS_ELAPSED is only based on news stories from a particular package (Dow Jones Edition, Web Edition, or PR Edition)

mws50_ens_elapsed_2.description: EVENT NOVELTY ELAPSED TIME - The number of milliseconds between the first story and the current story in an event novelty chain. The first story in a chain will always be given a value of zero milliseconds (ENS_ELAPSED = 0). Subsequent stories in the same event novelty chain will receive higher values indicating the number of milliseconds elapsed since the first news story reporting the event. ENS_ELAPSED is only based on news stories from a particular package (Dow Jones Edition, Web Edition, or PR Edition)

mws50_ens_key.description: An alphanumeric identifier that provides a way to chain or relate stories about the same categorized event for the same entities.

mws50_ens_similarity_gap.description: The number of days since a similar story was detected in this RPNA edition (Dow Jones Edition, Web Edition, or PR Edition). Values range between 0.00000 and 100.00000 inclusive. The value 100.00000 means that the most recent similar story occurred 100 or more days in the past. The value 0.00000 means a similar story exists with the exact same timestamp

mws50_ens_similarity_gap_2.description: The number of days since a similar story was detected in this RPNA edition (Dow Jones Edition, Web Edition, or PR Edition). Values range between 0.00000 and 100.00000 inclusive. The value 100.00000 means that the most recent similar story occurred 100 or more days in the past. The value 0.00000 means a similar story exists with the exact same timestamp

mws50_ess.description: EVENT SENTIMENT SCORE - A granular score between 0 and 100 that represents the news sentiment for a given entity by measuring various proxies sampled from the news. The score is determined by systematically matching stories typically categorized by financial experts as having short-term positive or negative financial or economic impact. Their ratings are encapsulated in an algorithm that generates a score range between 0-100 where higher values indicate more positive sentiment while values below 50 show negative sentiment.

mws50_ess_2.description: EVENT SENTIMENT SCORE - A granular score between 0 and 100 that represents the news sentiment for a given entity by measuring various proxies sampled from the news. The score is determined by systematically matching stories typically categorized by financial experts as having short-term positive or negative financial or economic impact. Their ratings are encapsulated in an algorithm that generates a score range between 0-100 where higher values indicate more positive sentiment while values below 50 show negative sentiment.

mws50_evaluation_method.description: A period of time used to measure changes from previous levels in an event.

mws50_g_ens.description: GLOBAL EVENT NOVELTY SCORE - A score between 0 and 100 that represents how "new" or novel a news story is within a 24-hour time window across all news providers covered by RavenPack

mws50_g_ens_2.description: GLOBAL EVENT NOVELTY SCORE - A score between 0 and 100 that represents how "new" or novel a news story is within a 24-hour time window across all news providers covered by RavenPack

mws50_g_ens_elapsed.description: GLOBAL EVENT NOVELTY ELAPSED TIME - The number of milliseconds between the first story and the current story in an event novelty chain across all news providers covered by RavenPack

mws50_g_ens_elapsed_2.description: GLOBAL EVENT NOVELTY ELAPSED TIME - The number of milliseconds between the first story and the current story in an event novelty chain across all news providers covered by RavenPack

mws50_g_ens_key.description: An alphanumeric identifier that provides a way to chain or relate stories about the same categorized event for the same entities across all news providers.

mws50_g_ens_similarity_gap.description: The number of days since a similar story was detected across all product editions (Dow Jones Edition, Web Edition, and PR Edition)

mws50_g_ens_similarity_gap_2.description: The number of days since a similar story was detected across all product editions (Dow Jones Edition, Web Edition, and PR Edition)

mws50_ghc_lna.description: ANALYST RECOMMENDATIONS & CHANGES (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents a change in recommendation by an analyst firm in the form of a numerical score

mws50_ghc_lna_2.description: ANALYST RECOMMENDATIONS & CHANGES (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents a change in recommendation by an analyst firm in the form of a numerical score

mws50_maturity.description: For events related to debt, this named attribute indicates the period of time for which a financial instrument remains outstanding.

mws50_news_type.description: Classifies the type of news story

mws50_news_type_2.description: Classifies the type of news story

mws50_nip.description: NEWS IMPACT PROJECTIONS (Equities Package Only) - A score taking values between 0 and 100 that represents the degree of impact a news flash has on the market over the following two-hour period Whether something is considered high or low depends on the time of day when the story arrived

mws50_nip_2.description: NEWS IMPACT PROJECTIONS (Equities Package Only) - A score taking values between 0 and 100 that represents the degree of impact a news flash has on the market over the following two-hour period Whether something is considered high or low depends on the time of day when the story arrived

mws50_position_name.description: The position held by an individual within the entity involved in a specific news event.

mws50_product_key.description: Identifies which subscription package contains the record

mws50_property.description: A named attribute of an event such as an entity, role, or string extracted from a matched event type. When applicable, the role played by the entity in the story is detected and tagged

mws50_qcm.description: MULTI CLASSIFIER FOR EQUITIES (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment based on th tone; applicable only towards the most relevant companies mentioned in a story. The score is derived from a combination of analytics values produced by the BMQ, BEE, BCA, and ANL-CHG classifiers

mws50_qcm_2.description: MULTI CLASSIFIER FOR EQUITIES (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment based on th tone; applicable only towards the most relevant companies mentioned in a story. The score is derived from a combination of analytics values produced by the BMQ, BEE, BCA, and ANL-CHG classifiers

mws50_qep.description: GLOBAL EQUITIES (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given news item according to the PEQ classifier, which specializes in identifying positive and negative words and phrases in articles about global equities

mws50_qep_2.description: GLOBAL EQUITIES (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given news item according to the PEQ classifier, which specializes in identifying positive and negative words and phrases in articles about global equities

mws50_qmb.description: EDITORIALS & COMMENTARY (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given story according to the BMQ classifier, which specializes in short commentary and editorials on global equity markets

mws50_qmb_2.description: EDITORIALS & COMMENTARY (Equities Package Only) - A score that represents the news sentiment of the given story according to the BMQ classifier, which specializes in short commentary and editorials on global equity markets

mws50_relevance.description: A score between 0-100 that indicates how strongly related the entity is to the underlying newsstory, with higher values indicating greater relevance Specifically, a value of 100 indicates that the entity identified plays a key role in the news story and is considered highly relevant

mws50_relevance_2.description: A score between 0-100 that indicates how strongly related the entity is to the underlying newsstory, with higher values indicating greater relevance Specifically, a value of 100 indicates that the entity identified plays a key role in the news story and is considered highly relevant

mws50_rp_story_event_count.description: Represents the total entity records published by RavenPack per news story

mws50_rp_story_event_count_2.description: Represents the total entity records published by RavenPack per news story

mws50_rp_story_event_index.description: Represents the order in which entity records are published by RavenPack per news story. This integer can be equal to or less than the RP_STORY_EVENT_COUNT

mws50_rp_story_event_index_2.description: Represents the order in which entity records are published by RavenPack per news story. This integer can be equal to or less than the RP_STORY_EVENT_COUNT

mws50_ssc.description: A sentiment score between 0 and 100 that represents the news sentiment of a given story by combining various sentiment analysis techniques

mws50_ssc_2.description: A sentiment score between 0 and 100 that represents the news sentiment of a given story by combining various sentiment analysis techniques

mws50_sub_type.description: A subdivision of a particular class of events

mws50_topic.description: A subject or theme of events detected

mws50_type.description: A class of events, the constituents of which share similar characteristics

mws50_vea.description: A value that represents the count of events for an entity (excluding neutral ones) measured over a rolling 91-day window in a particular package (Dow Jones, Web, or PR Editions). Only news items that match a RavenPack event category receiving an ESS score are included in the computation of AEV. Both events with an ESS score above and below 50 are counted by AEV, effectively signaling the volume of highly relevant news on the entity over the past 91 days. Events with ESS=50 are considered neutral and excluded from the computation

mws50_vea_2.description: A value that represents the count of events for an entity (excluding neutral ones) measured over a rolling 91-day window in a particular package (Dow Jones, Web, or PR Editions). Only news items that match a RavenPack event category receiving an ESS score are included in the computation of AEV. Both events with an ESS score above and below 50 are counted by AEV, effectively signaling the volume of highly relevant news on the entity over the past 91 days. Events with ESS=50 are considered neutral and excluded from the computation

news_volatility_projection_score.description: A score estimating the impact of a news flash on short-term market volatility.

non_neutral_event_count_rolling_window.description: Count of non-neutral events for an entity over a rolling 91-day window.

novelty_elapsed_milliseconds.description: Milliseconds between the first and current story in an event novelty chain.

novelty_similarity_gap_days.description: Number of days since a similar story was detected in a specific data package.

positive_event_ratio_score.description: Ratio of positive to total non-neutral events for an entity over a rolling window.
